---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";

const doors = [
  {
    quote: "I can't stop worrying.",
    title: "Anxiety & Overthinking",
    desc: "Thinking feels safe. Doing feels like a cliff.",
    href: "/personal-work/anxiety-overthinking",
  },
  {
    quote: "I can't decide, and it's wearing me out.",
    title: "Stay or Go",
    desc: "A marriage, a faith, a career. The question has been running your life for years.",
    href: "/personal-work/stay-or-go",
  },
  {
    quote: "I lost myself somewhere along the way.",
    title: "Coming Back to Yourself",
    desc: "The roles got louder than the person underneath them.",
    href: "/personal-work/coming-back-to-yourself",
  },
  {
    quote: "I keep holding myself back.",
    title: "Confidence & Self-Worth",
    desc: "You do plenty. You just don't believe in yourself.",
    href: "/personal-work/confidence-self-worth",
  },
  {
    quote: "I miss someone I love.",
    title: "The Distance Between You",
    desc: "They're still right here. Somehow they're still out of reach.",
    href: "/personal-work/the-distance-between-you",
  },
  {
    quote: "I don't trust my own reality anymore.",
    title: "Am I the Problem?",
    desc: "You replay conversations and come away less sure than when you started.",
    href: "/personal-work/am-i-the-problem",
  },
];
---

<Base title="Personal Work — Ennea Evolution" description="Counseling and coaching for people ready to understand their own lives. Start with the door that sounds most like you.">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Personal Work</p>
      <h1>Something in your life isn't quite adding up.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        You may not be able to name exactly what's wrong yet. Most people can't. You just know you're anxious, stuck,
        disconnected, exhausted, doubting yourself, or carrying the same question you've been carrying for years.
      </p>
      <p style="max-width:60ch;">You don't have to figure it out before you start. Just start with the one that sounds most like you.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DOORS -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="center" style="margin-bottom:2.75rem;">
        <p class="eyebrow">Pick the door that sounds like you</p>
      </div>
      <div class="door-grid">
        {doors.map((d) => (
          <a class="door-card" href={d.href}>
            <p class="door-quote">{d.quote}</p>
            <h3>{d.title}</h3>
            <p class="door-desc">{d.desc}</p>
            <span class="arrow-link">Explore <span class="arrow">→</span></span>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHY CONNECTED -->
  <section class="section bg-cream2">
    <div class="container narrow prose">
      <p class="eyebrow center">Why these struggles are so often connected</p>
      <p>At first they look unrelated. Anxiety. A relationship that aches. Self-doubt. Not being able to make a decision. Feeling far from yourself.</p>
      <p>Underneath, they're often the same thing wearing different clothes. Some part of you is protecting something. A belief that once made complete sense is still shaping what you do, even though the situation that created it has changed.</p>
      <p>That's why these struggles are so confusing. The pattern isn't irrational. It makes sense from the inside. And because it makes sense, fighting it usually doesn't work. Understanding it does.</p>
      <p>Most people already know their patterns. The question was never whether they exist. It's why they make so much sense to a part of you. Once that becomes clear, change gets easier — not because you're forcing yourself, but because you're finally working with yourself instead of against yourself.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT PEOPLE GET BACK -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow prose">
      <p class="eyebrow center">What people get back</p>
      <p>Most people come in focused on the problem: the anxiety, the relationship, the decision, the self-doubt. What they get back is usually bigger than that.</p>
      <p class="lead">They get themselves back.</p>
      <p>You stop arguing with yourself. You stop treating every decision like a verdict on your worth. You stop carrying relationships alone. You stop reacting to stories that feel true but aren't.</p>
      <p>And slowly, things start to make sense. Not just the problem you came in with. You.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section bg-teal center">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h2>You don't have to know the answer.</h2>
      <p style="color:#cfe0e2; max-width:55ch; margin-inline:auto;">
        You only have to recognize the question. Pick the door that sounds most like you. If you're not sure, we'll figure it out together.
      </p>
      <div class="btn-row" style="justify-content:center; margin-top:1.75rem;">
        <a href="/get-started" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .door-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: clamp(1rem, 2.2vw, 1.5rem);
  }
  .door-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    background: var(--paper);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: clamp(1.5rem, 2.5vw, 2rem);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
    color: var(--body);
    transition: transform 0.18s ease, box-shadow 0.18s ease, border-color 0.18s ease;
  }
  .door-card:hover { transform: translateY(-3px); box-shadow: var(--shadow-md); border-color: var(--line-strong); }
  .door-quote {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--marigold-600);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }
  .door-card h3 { color: var(--teal-900); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .door-desc { flex: 1; margin-bottom: 1rem; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) { .door-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } }
  @media (max-width: 560px) { .door-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
